<h3 class="card-title">Headings</h3>

<p class="lead">
  There are six kind of headings: <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>.
  <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> is the biggest. <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> is the smallest.
</p>

<p>
  The heading text is prefixed with a number octothorps (pound symbol <code>#</code>)
  and a <code>space</code>. The number of octothorps corresponds to the the level of heading:
  one octothorp <code>#</code> makes an <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>,
  two octothorps <code>##</code> makes an <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code>,
  etc.
</p>

<p>A heading should always have a blank line above and below it.</p>

<pre class="card bg-light"><code class="card-body"># This is an H1
## This is an H2
### This is an H3
#### This is an H4
##### This is an H5
###### This is an H6</code></pre>

<hr>

<h4>Example Markdown</h4>

<pre class="card bg-light"><code class="card-body"># Stuff and Things</code></pre>

<h4>Generated HTML</h4>

<pre class="card bg-light"><code class="card-body">&lt;h1&gt;Stuff and Things&lt;/h1&gt;</code></pre>

<h4>Rendered HTML</h4>

<div class="card pt-3 pb-2 px-4">
  <h1>Stuff and Things</h1>
</div>
